## Responsive Typography
Responsive classes are available with `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, and `xl:` prefixes for all text utilities.

## Usage Examples
```html
<!-- Using semantic classes -->
<h1 class="heading-2xl">Page Title</h1>
<p class="body-md">Body text content</p>

<!-- Using utility classes -->
<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Section Heading</h2>
<p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Small helper text</p>

<!-- Responsive typography -->
<h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl lg:text-4xl">Responsive heading</h1>
```

## Best Practices
1. **Use semantic classes** like `.heading-lg` for consistent component styling
2. **Use utility classes** for one-off text styling
3. **Follow the type scale** - use provided font sizes for visual hierarchy
4. **Pair font sizes with appropriate line heights** using the system
5. **Use responsive typography** for better mobile experience
6. **Prefer semibold** over bold for better readability at smaller sizes